did.unittitle: School of Architecture, Yale University, photographs of events, activities, and individuals

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The materials consist of group photographs of classes and pictures of classroom scenes.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 19-H (YRG 19-H), Audio-visual materials and memorabilia documenting the Yale School of Architecture.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The materials were transferred from the School of Architecture, 2003-2008.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

Original born digital files, as well as preservation masters, may not be accessed due to their fragility. Researchers must consult use copies, or if none exist request that they be made. Born digital files cannot be accessed remotely. System requirements include a Manuscripts and Archives computer and file viewing software.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: School of Architecture, Yale University, Photographs of Events, Activities, and Individuals (RU 934). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The materials are arranged by accession.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials consist of group photographs of classes and pictures of classroom scenes.
